  "questions": [
    {
      "text": "A 33-year-old woman reports a 2-week history of painless jaundice, pruritus, and dark urine. She denies abdominal pain, nausea, vomiting, or weight loss. She has no history of liver disease.\nHer medical history is significant for a sinus infection, 4 weeks ago, treated with amoxicillin-clavulanate. She does not take any over-the-counter medications or herbal supplements. She does not use intravenous drugs or drink alcohol. Her mother has heart disease.\nOn examination, she is alert and oriented. Her blood pressure is 100/55 mm Hg, and her BMI is 28. Her abdomen is soft and nontender, with no hepatosplenomegaly. The sclerae are icteric. Skin examination reveals no rashes. Asterixis is not present. Ultrasound of the right upper quadrant is normal.\nHer international normalized ratio is 1.1. Other notable laboratory results are as follows:\n\n\n\nPatient value\nReference range\n\n\n\nAlananine aminotransferase (U/liter)\n185\n0–35\n\n\n\nAspartate aminotransferase (U/liter)\n121\n0–35\n\n\n\nAlkaline phosphatase (U/liter)\n440\n30–120\n\n\n\nTotal bilirubin (mg/dL)\n5.5\n0.3–1.0\n\n\n\nDirect bilirubin (mg/dL)\n4.8\n0.1–0.3\n\n\nLeukocyte count (per mm3)\n7700\n4500–11,000\n\n\nHematocrit (%)\n39.0\n36.0–46.0\n\n\nPlatelet count (per mm3)\n250,000\n150,000–350,000\n\n\nWhich one of the following management strategies is most appropriate for this patient?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Referral for liver transplantation"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Watchful waiting"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Ursodeoxycholic acid"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Prednisone"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 3,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5I0iWh&anker=Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-learningcard-id=\"5I0iWh\" data-anker=\"Z5b9118463e989a0db84a025ca7a2606b\" data-section-id=\"PL1WBh0\" data-sememe-id=\"ty0XSi\">Endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography</a> is not indicated in this setting; the normal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=np07JS&anker=Zf438ec9414d78af41b73470a49bb8221\" data-learningcard-id=\"np07JS\" data-anker=\"Zf438ec9414d78af41b73470a49bb8221\" data-section-id=\"ACcRue0\" data-sememe-id=\"g9bF5D\">right upper quadrant</a> on <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4n03tg&anker=Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-learningcard-id=\"4n03tg\" data-anker=\"Z4254d71ea91bb85a18eeeaaf5e7adbef\" data-sememe-id=\"fK0kfS\">ultrasound</a> makes a biliary lesion unlikely to be the cause of this patient’s presentation.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>If the <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> blood tests do not improve, consideration of other causes of abnormal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> blood tests should be pursued. Rarely, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> can develop, necessitating <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gn0Fsg&anker=Z9f6395c3522788404ead5787426b6090\" data-learningcard-id=\"gn0Fsg\" data-anker=\"Z9f6395c3522788404ead5787426b6090\" data-section-id=\"60cjSa0\" data-sememe-id=\"3QYSDK\">liver transplantation</a>. Patients should be monitored for the development of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> and <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span> and referred to a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=gn0Fsg&anker=Z9f6395c3522788404ead5787426b6090\" data-learningcard-id=\"gn0Fsg\" data-anker=\"Z9f6395c3522788404ead5787426b6090\" data-section-id=\"60cjSa0\" data-sememe-id=\"3QYSDK\">liver transplant</a> center if either of those conditions develops.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) CORRECT:</h4>Drug-induced <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span> is common. Almost any medication can lead to abnormal <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zec7198aab35043cf581b97bde4bf916f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zec7198aab35043cf581b97bde4bf916f\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"mmYVTp\">liver function test</a> results. According to the Drug-Induced <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">Liver</a> Injury (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>) Network, the most commonly implicated drug classes are <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z4660f53b2b0c85aa3f9ab01bdf3f14f3\">antibiotics</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=lp0vpS&anker=Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-learningcard-id=\"lp0vpS\" data-anker=\"Z0111aade770ed6f7d136b455de1d6c1f\" data-section-id=\"1Cc2Ie0\" data-sememe-id=\"6SXj0B\">central nervous system</a> agents, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-N0Ddg&anker=Zcd438fb2824eb980a6d8940c193890ba\" data-learningcard-id=\"-N0Ddg\" data-anker=\"Zcd438fb2824eb980a6d8940c193890ba\" data-sememe-id=\"XL09wg\">antiepileptic</a> or <span data-sememe-id=\"Qu1uIi0\">psychotropic drugs</span>. In a study of 300 patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"lIdv1r0\">amoxicillin-clavulanate</span> was the single most common causative agent, accounting for 23 cases.<br><br>The pattern of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> injury associated with <span data-sememe-id=\"lIdv1r0\">amoxicillin-clavulanate</span> is typically <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z3811ba77a88bcd2cc789df34c5379055\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z3811ba77a88bcd2cc789df34c5379055\" data-section-id=\"EXW8-P0\" data-sememe-id=\"Vu0GJ3\">cholestatic</a>, with substantial elevations in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z78c098e284dee4ae95afddad9ababaa4\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z78c098e284dee4ae95afddad9ababaa4\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"rmYfSp\">alkaline phosphatase</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z07a8a4f4a850245bf742b6a98121b3e0\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z07a8a4f4a850245bf742b6a98121b3e0\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"HmYKSp\">bilirubin</a>, but only mild elevations in <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"MmYMTp\">aminotransferases</a>. However, hepatocellular and mixed patterns of injury can occur. Symptoms of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> related to <span data-sememe-id=\"lIdv1r0\">amoxicillin-clavulanate</span> typically occur after cessation of the drug. In a study of 69 patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> related to <span data-sememe-id=\"lIdv1r0\">amoxicillin-clavulanate</span>, the mean time from cessation of the drug to onset of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"bu0Hp3\">jaundice</a> was 15 days, with a range of 2 to 55 days.<br><br>In a patient with suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> who has clearly been exposed to a precipitating drug, the best management approach is to discontinue the offending agent and monitor <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> blood tests until they return to normal (<span data-sememe-id=\"2ycTeU0\">watchful waiting</span>). Many centers will also use <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a>, even in patients who are not suspected of having <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=BN0zWg&anker=Za3da7a7c0e6eb1d1d781615b1c2c7af3\" data-learningcard-id=\"BN0zWg\" data-anker=\"Za3da7a7c0e6eb1d1d781615b1c2c7af3\" data-section-id=\"Ykcnmc0\" data-sememe-id=\"gvYFzI\">acetaminophen</a>-induced <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> and especially in those with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a>.<br><br><span class=\"wichtig\"><b>Key learning point:</b></span> The most appropriate <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Zd0447ed08a4b2fe2f49d111362f5a560\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Zd0447ed08a4b2fe2f49d111362f5a560\" data-section-id=\"-8WD6M0\">management of drug-induced liver injury</a> without <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span> or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> is discontinuation of the offending medication and <span data-sememe-id=\"2ycTeU0\">watchful waiting</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=MS0MZf&anker=Z616485de8e020be6a556a6fc22c74cf9\" data-learningcard-id=\"MS0MZf\" data-anker=\"Z616485de8e020be6a556a6fc22c74cf9\" data-section-id=\"9A0NNi\" data-sememe-id=\"aE0Q83\">Ursodeoxycholic acid</a> is used to treat <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=MS0MZf&anker=Z28d0176d7f64a91d96a0228f774e39e4\" data-learningcard-id=\"MS0MZf\" data-anker=\"Z28d0176d7f64a91d96a0228f774e39e4\" data-sememe-id=\"B40zlT\">primary biliary cholangitis</a>, not <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Studies have not shown a clear benefit of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">glucocorticoids</a> in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>.</div>",
