    {
      "text": "A 42-year-old woman presents to the ED with 7 days of nausea, fatigue, and right upper quadrant abdominal discomfort after taking oral itraconazole for toenail dermatophyte infection for the past 6 weeks. She denies alcohol use and reports no other medication use. Vital signs are BP, 118/72 mm Hg; P, 82; R, 16; T, 37.2°C (99.0°F). On examination, she has scleral icterus and mild hepatic tenderness. Her mental status is normal, and no asterixis is observed. Laboratory results show ALT 1,120 U/L, AST 1,050 U/L, total bilirubin 4.5 mg/dL, INR 1.9, and creatinine is 1.0 mg/dL. Abdominal ultrasound shows no biliary obstruction. Viral hepatitis panel is negative. What is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Discharge for close outpatient follow-up with hepatology"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Start IV N-acetylcysteine infusion"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Admit for glucocorticoid therapy"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Admit for observation"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Give single-dose activated charcoal"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>While outpatient follow-up is reasonable for patients with mild <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> and preserved <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zaee1e125a18bbca6cdd29f11cf34c74d\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zaee1e125a18bbca6cdd29f11cf34c74d\" data-section-id=\"c8calV0\">hepatic function</a>, this patient demonstrates significant <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z88f5ae99086ac44bd78f75b774ae547a\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z88f5ae99086ac44bd78f75b774ae547a\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"XQ19ug0\">hyperbilirubinemia</a> and impaired synthetic function (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-section-id=\"S61y430\" data-sememe-id=\"Cr0qjh\">INR</a> = 1.9). Discharging her would risk missing early decompensation.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a> is indicated for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Z58fbab9a84c7c9ef0b226ec58881e66a\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Z58fbab9a84c7c9ef0b226ec58881e66a\" data-sememe-id=\"HbbKEH\">acetaminophen overdose</a>, and is also considered in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> related to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>) from other causes. This patient with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> from <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6m0jgg&anker=Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"6m0jgg\" data-anker=\"Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-section-id=\"_315Og0\" data-sememe-id=\"nWY7NL\">itraconazole</a> has <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> but no signs of <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span>, and thus does not meet criteria for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a> is therefore not indicated at this point.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">Glucocorticoids</a> are considered in immune-mediated <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span>, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bs0Hth&anker=Z0a5a570644776cd8880ae14f14498dd5\" data-learningcard-id=\"bs0Hth\" data-anker=\"Z0a5a570644776cd8880ae14f14498dd5\" data-sememe-id=\"UIbbXE\">DRESS</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qM0Cpg&anker=Z69d84d36a6a40eb875c877624d34e023\" data-learningcard-id=\"qM0Cpg\" data-anker=\"Z69d84d36a6a40eb875c877624d34e023\" data-section-id=\"15c2Q10\" data-sememe-id=\"2oWTYm0\">checkpoint inhibitor</a>–induced <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z1d95c73e140242a536db072ff6adf252\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z1d95c73e140242a536db072ff6adf252\" data-section-id=\"L8bwMv\" data-sememe-id=\"LI0wWh\">tyrosine kinase inhibitor</a>–related <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> injury. They may also be considered in patients with autoimmune features on <span data-sememe-id=\"xWbEns\">liver biopsy</span>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">Glucocorticoids</a> are not typically indicated for intraconazole <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span> in the absence of <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">biopsy</span> evidence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z5b9131be1bebb97e50e5de18dcc8b057\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z5b9131be1bebb97e50e5de18dcc8b057\" data-section-id=\"S_Xyn00\">autoimmunity</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6m0jgg&anker=Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"6m0jgg\" data-anker=\"Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-section-id=\"_315Og0\" data-sememe-id=\"nWY7NL\">Itraconazole</a> is a known cause of severe <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span>. This patient demonstrates a <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uF0pP3&anker=Z9aaeaa8b71475fed3f47603398b70dd2\" data-learningcard-id=\"uF0pP3\" data-anker=\"Z9aaeaa8b71475fed3f47603398b70dd2\" data-section-id=\"cvWa_M0\" data-sememe-id=\"c7dakr0\">hepatocellular pattern of injury</a> with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"MmYMTp\">transaminases</a> &gt;1,000, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z88f5ae99086ac44bd78f75b774ae547a\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z88f5ae99086ac44bd78f75b774ae547a\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"XQ19ug0\">hyperbilirubinemia</a>, and impaired synthetic function (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-section-id=\"S61y430\" data-sememe-id=\"Cr0qjh\">INR</a> 1.9). Although she has no <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span>, the presence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> indicates an increased risk of adverse outcomes. Hospitalization for monitoring and supportive care of patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> is recommended in patients with severe <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=7J04vS&anker=Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"7J04vS\" data-anker=\"Z2f0b48ef2acaab783b03e4c8d2404f90\">nausea and vomiting</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ig0Y92&anker=Zbd78324053c153c16ea5cb2574249398\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ig0Y92\" data-anker=\"Zbd78324053c153c16ea5cb2574249398\" data-section-id=\"rJXfv_\" data-sememe-id=\"g40FiT\">dehydration</a>, <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span>, and/or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=ur0pQh&anker=Za006c42a19dc225d40b70e9f026aa925\" data-learningcard-id=\"ur0pQh\" data-anker=\"Za006c42a19dc225d40b70e9f026aa925\" data-section-id=\"C61qM30\" data-sememe-id=\"d4boRF\">Activated charcoal</a> is useful only if administered within hours of ingestion to limit absorption. In cases of chronic drug exposure such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=6m0jgg&anker=Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-learningcard-id=\"6m0jgg\" data-anker=\"Zc8a824377940a4f33da3348d745697e6\" data-section-id=\"_315Og0\" data-sememe-id=\"nWY7NL\">itraconazole</a> use over weeks, charcoal is ineffective.</div>",
