      "correct_choice_id": 1,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) CORRECT:</h4>Correct – This patient has suspected <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>) from antittuberculosis drugs and presents with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> evidenced by <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Z13fa66b31f3bc2f3afbc7bdd5cd21792\" data-section-id=\"S61y430\" data-sememe-id=\"Cr0qjh\">INR</a> 2.4) and <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span> (confusion, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x30Ekf&anker=Z52c37a2c3343e9337574fa16e8405666\" data-learningcard-id=\"x30Ekf\" data-anker=\"Z52c37a2c3343e9337574fa16e8405666\" data-section-id=\"aIXQYz\" data-sememe-id=\"2JaTtl\">asterixis</a>). He requires admission for close monitoring and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zc881a21acbc9e7c0e7a30e92fbf3da05\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zc881a21acbc9e7c0e7a30e92fbf3da05\" data-section-id=\"8bWOvP0\">treatment of acute liver failure</a>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a> for at least 3 days is considered in all patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> related to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>. </div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">Glucocorticoids</a> are considered in immune-mediated <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span>, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=bs0Hth&anker=Z0a5a570644776cd8880ae14f14498dd5\" data-learningcard-id=\"bs0Hth\" data-anker=\"Z0a5a570644776cd8880ae14f14498dd5\" data-sememe-id=\"UIbbXE\">DRESS</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=qM0Cpg&anker=Z69d84d36a6a40eb875c877624d34e023\" data-learningcard-id=\"qM0Cpg\" data-anker=\"Z69d84d36a6a40eb875c877624d34e023\" data-section-id=\"15c2Q10\" data-sememe-id=\"2oWTYm0\">checkpoint inhibitor</a>–induced <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span>, or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=4m03fg&anker=Z1d95c73e140242a536db072ff6adf252\" data-learningcard-id=\"4m03fg\" data-anker=\"Z1d95c73e140242a536db072ff6adf252\" data-section-id=\"L8bwMv\" data-sememe-id=\"LI0wWh\">tyrosine kinase inhibitor</a>–related <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> injury. They may also be considered in patients with autoimmune features on <span data-sememe-id=\"xWbEns\">liver biopsy</span>. <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=km0mfg&anker=Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-learningcard-id=\"km0mfg\" data-anker=\"Z521ecba6f9748e7fed6b743a73ccfabd\" data-sememe-id=\"4L03Bg\">Glucocorticoids</a> are not typically used in standard cases of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>), such as  <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span> from antituberculosis drugs, in the absence of <span data-sememe-id=\"sebtZG\">biopsy</span> evidence of <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=x50Emg&anker=Z5b9131be1bebb97e50e5de18dcc8b057\" data-learningcard-id=\"x50Emg\" data-anker=\"Z5b9131be1bebb97e50e5de18dcc8b057\" data-section-id=\"S_Xyn00\">autoimmunity</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<span data-sememe-id=\"xWbEns\">Liver biopsy</span> is not routinely required for <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a> diagnosis. It may be considered to increase diagnostic certainty (e.g., if <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> injury persists despite discontinuation of the offending drug) or assess for alternative diagnoses (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=JM0spg&anker=Z0a72857d0e75c47a1e24539ad2f3f291\" data-learningcard-id=\"JM0spg\" data-anker=\"Z0a72857d0e75c47a1e24539ad2f3f291\" data-sememe-id=\"Ho0KWS\">autoimmune hepatitis</a>) but is premature in this patient at this point.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) INCORRECT:</h4>While admission is appropriate given the patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> with <span data-sememe-id=\"bRcHlX0\">encephalopathy</span> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=8T0Os2&anker=Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-learningcard-id=\"8T0Os2\" data-anker=\"Z5a3cc6f90267ccb75d4d2c02be76da5a\" data-sememe-id=\"7P04TT\">coagulopathy</a>, observation alone is inadequate. Another specific intervention is typically considered in patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> related to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">drug-induced liver injury</a> beyond supportive monitoring.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>\n<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ym0nVg&anker=Z1de5d1df48f548f9d227c6743af88c42\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ym0nVg\" data-anker=\"Z1de5d1df48f548f9d227c6743af88c42\" data-section-id=\"oBX0b00\" data-sememe-id=\"cWYa4L\">Cholestyramine</a> is specifically used to enhance drug elimination in patients with persistent <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z3811ba77a88bcd2cc789df34c5379055\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z3811ba77a88bcd2cc789df34c5379055\" data-section-id=\"EXW8-P0\" data-sememe-id=\"Vu0GJ3\">cholestasis</a> due to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=-f0DK2&anker=Zf1b21bb101c4fafa37cf68bb503896a0\" data-learningcard-id=\"-f0DK2\" data-anker=\"Zf1b21bb101c4fafa37cf68bb503896a0\" data-section-id=\"wj0hcT\" data-sememe-id=\"PlXWCy\">leflunomide</a> <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span>.  It is not indicated in this patient.</div>",
