      "text": "A 42-year-old man comes to the physician because of yellowish discoloration of his skin and dark urine for 3 days. He was diagnosed with pulmonary tuberculosis 2 weeks ago and started on a regimen consisting of isoniazid, rifampin, pyrazinamide, and ethambutol. He has a history of alcohol use disorder and consumes approximately six alcoholic beverages daily but states that he stopped drinking 1 month ago. His temperature is 37.5°C (99.5°F), pulse is 88/min, respirations are 16/min, and blood pressure is 118/76 mm Hg. Physical examination shows scleral icterus and mild right upper quadrant tenderness to palpation. The remainder of the examination shows no abnormalities. Laboratory studies show:\n\n\nProthrombin time\n13.5 seconds\n\n\nSerum\n\n\n\n Bilirubin\n\n\n\n Total\n4.2 mg/dL\n\n\n Direct\n2.8 mg/dL\n\n\n AST\n380 U/L\n\n\n ALT\n450 U/L\n\n\n Alkaline phosphatase\n110 U/L\n\n\nWhich of the following is the most appropriate next step in management?",
      "choices": [
        {
          "id": 1,
          "text": "Continue all medications and monitor liver function weekly"
        },
        {
          "id": 2,
          "text": "Discontinue pyrazinamide and continue isoniazid, rifampin, and ethambutol"
        },
        {
          "id": 3,
          "text": "Discontinue all medications and restart only isoniazid and rifampin when liver function normalizes"
        },
        {
          "id": 4,
          "text": "Discontinue all medications and initiate a different regimen after liver function normalize"
        },
        {
          "id": 5,
          "text": "Add N-acetylcysteine to the current tuberculosis regimen"
        }
      ],
      "correct_choice_id": 4,
      "solution": "<div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>A) INCORRECT:</h4>Continuing all medications with weekly monitoring may be appropriate for mild, asymptomatic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zde6636a7a9eaab224426560b3e3b2b4c\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"MmYMTp\">transaminase</a> elevations without symptoms, such as <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"bu0Hp3\">jaundice</a>. This patient has clinical and biochemical evidence of acute <span data-sememe-id=\"VpcGoW0\">hepatitis</span> (<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=jS0_z2&anker=Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-learningcard-id=\"jS0_z2\" data-anker=\"Z5f49d92f52d702a9bee9b2538ad7b454\" data-section-id=\"Gx0BBR\" data-sememe-id=\"bu0Hp3\">jaundice</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=np07JS&anker=Zf438ec9414d78af41b73470a49bb8221\" data-learningcard-id=\"np07JS\" data-anker=\"Zf438ec9414d78af41b73470a49bb8221\" data-section-id=\"ACcRue0\" data-sememe-id=\"g9bF5D\">RUQ</a> <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=xN0EWg&anker=Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-learningcard-id=\"xN0EWg\" data-anker=\"Zd673a3f7ee36023aab5a267899e984cc\" data-section-id=\"NBX-a00\">pain</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=uF0pP3&anker=Z2f43b8b9dc95cdb5bd93da3c354a3916\" data-learningcard-id=\"uF0pP3\" data-anker=\"Z2f43b8b9dc95cdb5bd93da3c354a3916\" data-sememe-id=\"GlXByy\">transaminitis</a>), so ongoing exposure to <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxic</span> drugs risks further <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> damage.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>B) INCORRECT:</h4>Discontinuing only <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-section-id=\"4jc30c0\" data-sememe-id=\"-C0DuR\">pyrazinamide</a> while continuing <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-section-id=\"PjcW0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"_C05uR\">isoniazid</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-section-id=\"jjc_Zc0\" data-sememe-id=\"zC0ruR\">rifampin</a> is not appropriate because both <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-section-id=\"PjcW0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"_C05uR\">isoniazid</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-section-id=\"jjc_Zc0\" data-sememe-id=\"zC0ruR\">rifampin</a> can independently cause significant <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxicity</span>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>C) INCORRECT:</h4>Selectively restarting <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-section-id=\"PjcW0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"_C05uR\">isoniazid</a> and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-section-id=\"jjc_Zc0\" data-sememe-id=\"zC0ruR\">rifampin</a> after <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zaee1e125a18bbca6cdd29f11cf34c74d\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zaee1e125a18bbca6cdd29f11cf34c74d\" data-section-id=\"c8calV0\">liver function</a> normalization is not recommended in symptomatic <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>, as these agents are <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxic</span>. Although sequential <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=dk0o5T&anker=Z82bfe49997498bb32f56bc1949a27eb2\" data-learningcard-id=\"dk0o5T\" data-anker=\"Z82bfe49997498bb32f56bc1949a27eb2\" data-section-id=\"VGWGy50\" data-sememe-id=\"kndmtq0\">challenge-rechallenge testing</a> may be considered in mild, asymptomatic cases, restarting two <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxic</span> agents is not appropriate.</div><div><h4 style='color: #34d399; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>D) CORRECT:</h4>Combining <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-section-id=\"PjcW0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"_C05uR\">isoniazid</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-section-id=\"jjc_Zc0\" data-sememe-id=\"zC0ruR\">rifampin</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-section-id=\"4jc30c0\" data-sememe-id=\"-C0DuR\">pyrazinamide</a> is a well-known <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z7e6abca5bc7d24ec7bbf90ce5cd9db24\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z7e6abca5bc7d24ec7bbf90ce5cd9db24\" data-section-id=\"A8WR6M0\">cause of DILI</a>, particularly in those with underlying <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> disease or <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=KP0UfT&anker=Zbd9d04087809541456b783e902516f0a\" data-learningcard-id=\"KP0UfT\" data-anker=\"Zbd9d04087809541456b783e902516f0a\" data-section-id=\"Id1Yrf0\" data-sememe-id=\"MRbMnt\">heavy alcohol use</a>. The first step in management is to <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>discontinue the offending agents </b></span>(<a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Ze97f4360f6ecf96cf0b3b580ad4c43eb\" data-section-id=\"PjcW0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"_C05uR\">isoniazid</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z965e7647077a8d15304b03fd24ad2f90\" data-section-id=\"jjc_Zc0\" data-sememe-id=\"zC0ruR\">rifampin</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z72e6a6e433facb529af773975a022c8f\" data-section-id=\"4jc30c0\" data-sememe-id=\"-C0DuR\">pyrazinamide</a>) to prevent further <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> damage, including progression to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a>. Once this patient's <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=Ln0wFg&anker=Zec7198aab35043cf581b97bde4bf916f\" data-learningcard-id=\"Ln0wFg\" data-anker=\"Zec7198aab35043cf581b97bde4bf916f\" data-section-id=\"9acN5a0\" data-sememe-id=\"mmYVTp\">liver function tests</a> normalize, a <span class=\"wichtig\"><b>new, less <span data-sememe-id=\"uiWptO0\">hepatotoxic</span> regimen</b></span> (e.g., <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z68fe33ebd77ce746cdd73d561168875d\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z68fe33ebd77ce746cdd73d561168875d\" data-section-id=\"kjcm0c0\" data-sememe-id=\"Zx0ZER\">ethambutol</a>, <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Zbaa4e57f76db10e58ace67e2d9646484\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Zbaa4e57f76db10e58ace67e2d9646484\" data-section-id=\"hjccZc0\" data-sememe-id=\"rOafFk\">streptomycin</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=mm0VTg&anker=Z6b160289536b8a7a7a2c161a02014e7c\" data-learningcard-id=\"mm0VTg\" data-anker=\"Z6b160289536b8a7a7a2c161a02014e7c\" data-section-id=\"VjcGzX0\" data-sememe-id=\"lL0vBg\">fluoroquinolones</a>) must be initiated to treat his <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=5h0ief&anker=Z4e2e25544038f990795073066ccfba2b\" data-learningcard-id=\"5h0ief\" data-anker=\"Z4e2e25544038f990795073066ccfba2b\" data-section-id=\"-p1DH30\" data-sememe-id=\"iC0J7R\">active tuberculosis</a>.</div><div><h4 style='color: #f87171; font-weight: bold; margin-top: 16px; font-size: 1.125rem;'>E) INCORRECT:</h4>Although <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a> may be considered in all patients with <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=zr0rPh&anker=Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-learningcard-id=\"zr0rPh\" data-anker=\"Zdad4c0a90381d600be596191b07e31eb\" data-sememe-id=\"6ZbjcH\">acute liver failure</a> related to <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=HF0Kj3&anker=Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-learningcard-id=\"HF0Kj3\" data-anker=\"Z21a6140219cde60c18e2be6077c82235\" data-sememe-id=\"MDXMUZ0\">DILI</a>, starting <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=oF00Q3&anker=Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-learningcard-id=\"oF00Q3\" data-anker=\"Za0cf6b9c5885e1a32cb577aa3e2fb8d7\" data-section-id=\"FYdgIo0\" data-sememe-id=\"7R04of\">N-acetylcysteine</a> therapy without discontinuing the offending agents is not appropriate and risks further <a href=\"https://www.amboss.com/us/library#xid=j60_kS&anker=Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\" data-learningcard-id=\"j60_kS\" data-anker=\"Zd0ed3eb208321943f24b364e0a464294\">liver</a> damage.</div>",
      "hint": "Hyperbilirubinemia, marked transaminase elevation, and hepatic tenderness shortly after starting antituberculosis therapy raise concern for drug-induced liver injury (DILI). Alcohol use disorder increases susceptibility to DILI.",
